30/08/2006
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- On Wednesday (30 August) the Koha Ditore daily reported that UN special envoy for Kosovo status talks Martti Ahtisaari will likely complete the draft framework of ideas to resolve the status issue by 7 September. Before then, he reportedly plans to visit both Pristina and Belgrade again to try to find some compromise regarding decentralisation and minority rights. 
In Belgrade Wednesday, the Serbian government plans to ask parliament to hold an emergency session on Kosovo. At the meeting, the negotiation team will present its report on the progress of the Kosovo status discussions, said the government's Media Office Director Srdan Duric. (Albanian News - 30/08/06; Tanjug, B92 - 29/08/06) 
